observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Management:
16. Authority for the entitlement of the allowance/office order/authority to report for work;
17. Daily Time Records with Biometric printouts/copies of logbook or Certificate of Attendance in the COVID Facility/Center by their immediate supervisor during the period of claims;
18. Accomplishment reports indicating the number of COVID patients attended to in a day;
19. For health workers not directly catering to COVID-19 patients, an explanation as to the scientific basis for the premise that healthcare workers not directly catering to COVID-19 patients are equally exposed to COVID-19 and can be considered “in contact with COVID-19 patients”, and thus should be given the SRA.
20. Require the Municipal Accountant-Designate to reclassify the payment of SRA payments of permanent and contractual employees amounting to ₱478,636.28 from Hazard Pay and Donations to Other Personnel Benefits and Other Maintenance and Operating Expenses in the CY 2021 Statement of Financial Performance.
